Jiangxi will train 10,000 rural elementary school teachers of music, sports and beauty in 3 years - Xinhua Xinhua News Agency Nanchang, May 22 (Reporter Chen Yushan) reporter recently learned from the Jiangxi Provincial Department of Education, in order to enhance the shortage of subject teachers to ensure the ability to achieve balanced development of compulsory education in rural areas, since 2016, Jiangxi Province plans to spend 3 years for the province's rural (township and below) each elementary school training qualified music, art, and Physical education teachers each 1, a total of 10,000. It is understood that the target of this training for rural elementary school in Jiangxi province under 45 years of age with the knowledge base or talent of music, art and physical education subjects, can also serve as music, art and physical education courses of other subject teachers. Through training, so that they master the basic knowledge and teaching skills of teaching the subject of music, sports and beauty, update teaching ideas and concepts, master modern teaching methods, improve the ability to teach the subject, the ability to design activities, campus culture and self-development capabilities, the construction of a multi-talented team of teachers of music, sports and beauty, to alleviate the problem of lack of rural teachers of music, sports and beauty. To ensure the quality and effectiveness of training, Jiangxi also plans to train one each of music, art and physical education for 100 counties (cities and districts) in the province's elementary school, a total of 300 trainers, to comprehensively improve their teaching demonstration and leading ability, the ability to design and organize teaching and research activities, the ability to administer training, and the ability to build online training workshops, to play the role of professor, demonstration, guidance and supervision.
